## 📊 ANALYSIS DOCUMENTATION

### Requirement Specification Template
```markdown
# REQ-[DOMAIN]-[NUMBER]: [Title]

## Overview
Brief description of business need

## User Story
As a: [User type]
I want: [Capability]
So that: [Business value]

## Functional Requirements
### FR-1: [Specific requirement]
- Description: [Detailed explanation]
- Input: [What comes in]
- Processing: [What happens]
- Output: [What goes out]
- Performance: <100ms required

## Non-Functional Requirements
### NFR-1: Performance
- Response time: <100ms
- Throughput: 1000+ RPS
- Availability: 99.9%

### NFR-2: Quality
- Zero mocks in testing
- 90% test coverage
- Crisis recovery: <48hr

## Data Requirements
### Entity: [Name]
- Fields: [List with types]
- Validation: [Rules]
- Relationships: [To other entities]
- Tenant: Isolated per tenant

## Integration Requirements
### System: [External system]
- Protocol: [REST/GraphQL/etc]
- Authentication: [Method]
- Contract: [Validation required]
- Error handling: [Recovery pattern]

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Functional requirements met
- [ ] Performance targets achieved
- [ ] Zero mocks in tests
- [ ] Integration validated
- [ ] Crisis scenario tested

## Risks & Mitigations
### Risk: [Potential issue]
- Probability: [High/Medium/Low]
- Impact: [Critical/Major/Minor]
- Mitigation: [Prevention strategy]
- Pattern: [From which platform]
```

### Process Flow Documentation
```yaml
The Learning:
  Clear flows prevent confusion

Flow Template:
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[User Action] --> B{Validation}
    B -->|Valid| C[Process]
    B -->|Invalid| D[Error Handling]
    C --> E{Check Performance}
    E -->|<100ms| F[Return Success]
    E -->|>100ms| G[Optimize + Alert]
    D --> H[Log + Return Error]
    G --> I[Crisis Protocol]
```

Documentation Includes:
  - Happy path
  - Error scenarios
  - Performance checks
  - Crisis triggers
  - Recovery flows
```

### Data Model Specification
```yaml
The Learning:
  Clear models prevent TreeNode-like crises

Model Template:
```sql
-- Table: [entity_name]
-- Purpose: [Business purpose]
-- Tenant: Isolated per tenant_id

CREATE TABLE entity_name (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    tenant_id UUID NOT NULL,  -- Multi-tenant

    -- Business fields
    field_name TYPE NOT NULL,

    -- Audit fields (required)
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    created_by UUID NOT NULL,
    updated_by UUID NOT NULL,

    -- Constraints
    CONSTRAINT fk_tenant FOREIGN KEY (tenant_id)
        REFERENCES tenants(id),

    -- Indexes for performance
    INDEX idx_tenant_id (tenant_id),
    INDEX idx_created_at (created_at)
);

-- Row Level Security
ALTER TABLE entity_name ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Performance target: <50ms queries
-- Expected volume: 1M+ records
```
```

